<!-- ============ SECTION 1: THE FULL LIFECYCLE ============ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-row">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="section-eyebrow">Full-Lifecycle RFID</span>
        <h2>Every unit gets a license plate. Every movement tracked.</h2>
        <p>Each tag carries an Electronic Product Code (EPC) — a UPC plus a unique serial. Ten identical shirts share one UPC but ten distinct EPCs, so they're ten trackable units, not a count of "10." That's why our stock counts are accurate and our loss prevention actually works.</p>
        <ul class="feature-bullets">
          <li>Source tagging: EPCs commissioned at the manufacturer, at the point of creation</li>
          <li>In-transit visibility: tagged containers tracked on the water, through customs, to the dock</li>
          <li>Receiving: tag, encode, and scan inbound shipments in one step — low-power reads capture only the shipment</li>
          <li>Unit control ledger: where every EPC was received, counted, transferred, sold, and whitelisted</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Book a demo <i class="ti ti-arrow-right"></i></a>
