<!-- ============ SECTION 2: SMART READING — POWER MODES ============ -->
<section class="section" style="padding-top: 0;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-row reverse">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="section-eyebrow">Intelligent Reading</span>
        <h2>Smart enough to know what it should read.</h2>
        <p>Receiving needs tight, low-power reads that capture only what's in front of you — not the 500 items on the racks behind. Stock counting needs the opposite: maximum range to sweep a whole store in minutes. The system switches automatically.</p>
        <ul class="feature-bullets">
          <li>Low-power for transactions: receiving, transfers, selling — reads only items within inches</li>
          <li>High-power for counting: full-store sweeps capture thousands of EPCs in minutes</li>
          <li>Confirmation logic: multiple reads per second before a tag counts — no phantom reads</li>
          <li>Anti-bleed: tags respond only to the antenna that energized them — no cross-reads between zones</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
