<!-- ============ SECTION 3: LOSS PREVENTION & EAS ============ -->
<section class="section" style="padding-top: 0;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-row">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="section-eyebrow">Loss Prevention & EAS</span>
        <h2>Blacklist every unit in the store. Whitelist it the instant it sells.</h2>
        <p>The unit control ledger is the foundation for real loss prevention. Every EPC in the store is on the blacklist. When a unit is sold at POS, it's instantly whitelisted — the signal reaches the EAS gate before the customer does. No false alarms. No ambiguity about who triggered it.</p>
        <ul class="feature-bullets">
          <li>Every EPC's status always known — blacklist/whitelist runs on the unit control ledger</li>
          <li>Instant POS-to-gate signal via a local server holding the ledger, pushed from cloud</li>
          <li>EAS gate integration with Checkpoint, Sensormatic, and others via API</li>
          <li>AI anomaly detection: tags moving toward an exit without a POS transaction trigger alerts</li>
          <li>Bag Check: customers scan their bag on the way out — discrepancies isolated with certainty</li>
        </ul>
